1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,420
L-Let's talk about this
somewhere else, not here.

2
00:00:03,503 --> 00:00:06,131
No! Let's talk here
so your son can hear everything!

3
00:00:06,756 --> 00:00:07,549
Well?!

4
00:00:07,632 --> 00:00:09,175
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

5
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:11,177
- Fine.
- [PAPER RUSTLING, RIPPING]

6
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,975
Do you think tearing that
will change the truth?

7
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:20,186
The truth is… you're a mistress!

8
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,397
And you're a bastard!

9
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:25,066
Shut up, will you? Shut up.

10
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:26,943
- [SLAP]
- Shut up!

11
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:27,902
What?!

12
00:00:28,737 --> 00:00:31,698
All my life, you've made me think
I was a product of sin.

13
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:33,575
That my mother committed a sin.

14
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:37,203
But the truth is, you're the mistress!

15
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:38,455
Stop it!

16
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:39,789
[VICTOR] What?

17
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:42,542
You want to know the truth?
Ask your mother!

18
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:43,918
Let's talk at home.

19
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:46,713
- Not here!
- Why? You're ashamed, huh?

20
00:00:46,796 --> 00:00:49,382
Were you ashamed
when you took everything from my mother?

21
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:52,010
How could you stomach that?

22
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:55,388
How could you fool all of us?

23
00:00:55,472 --> 00:00:57,015
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

24
00:00:57,098 --> 00:00:58,266
What's the truth, Ma?

25
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:02,645
Tell me, what's the truth?!

26
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:05,106
Ma!

27
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:09,569
What's the truth?!

28
00:01:09,652 --> 00:01:14,365
Alex, I only did it because…

29
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:31,341
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

30
00:01:44,395 --> 00:01:45,313
<i>Victor.</i>

31
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:49,776
<i>Victor, son.</i>

32
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:53,863
<i>From now on, you're going to live here.</i>

33
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:56,533
<i>Behave yourself, okay?</i>

34
00:01:58,535 --> 00:01:59,327
[SMOOCHES]

35
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:02,747
<i>Oh. Amelia.</i>

36
00:02:04,082 --> 00:02:05,125
<i>This is Victor.</i>

37
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:12,215
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

38
00:02:13,591 --> 00:02:19,013
[POUNDING NOISES]

39
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:20,390
[YOUNG VICTOR] <i>That's a nice toy.</i>

40
00:02:21,891 --> 00:02:28,731
[POUNDING NOISES]

41
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:33,820
<i>Hey! Don't touch that!</i>

42
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:35,280
<i>Do you know how to box?</i>

43
00:02:35,363 --> 00:02:38,700
<i>Yes, I want to become a boxer like Papa.</i>

44
00:02:38,783 --> 00:02:40,326
<i>- Are you good at it?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

45
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:43,705
[MAKES WHOOSHING SOUNDS]

46
00:02:43,788 --> 00:02:45,331
<i>See? I'm good, right?</i>

47
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,042
<i>Alex.</i>

48
00:02:50,169 --> 00:02:51,087
<i>Come here, son.</i>

49
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:53,715
<i>Listen.</i>

50
00:02:53,798 --> 00:02:54,966
<i>His name is Victor.</i>

51
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,260
<i>He's your brother.</i>

52
00:02:58,136 --> 00:02:59,345
<i>From now on,</i>

53
00:03:01,097 --> 00:03:02,432
<i>he will stay with us.</i>

54
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:06,269
<i>You now have a training buddy, Alex.</i>

55
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:08,646
<i>Isn't that great? Come here, son.</i>

56
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,565
[SMOOCHES]

57
00:03:10,648 --> 00:03:12,609
<i>I won't ask for anything more, Amelia.</i>

58
00:03:14,485 --> 00:03:15,570
<i>All I want</i>

59
00:03:16,571 --> 00:03:18,281
<i>is for you to be nice to Victor.</i>

60
00:03:19,073 --> 00:03:20,617
<i>You know money</i><i>is tight.</i>

61
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,201
<i>Why did you bring him here?</i>

62
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:24,954
<i>Doesn't his mother have any relatives?</i>

63
00:03:25,496 --> 00:03:26,831
<i>No, she doesn't.</i>

64
00:03:26,915 --> 00:03:29,125
<i>But I'd rather be with my son.</i>

65
00:03:29,792 --> 00:03:32,420
<i>There were barely any people</i>
<i>at Leonor's funeral.</i>

66
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:36,674
<i>Don't mention her name.</i>
<i>It's not necessary.</i>

67
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:40,303
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:41,554
<i>Amelia.</i>

69
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:43,848
<i>Victor is a good kid.</i>

70
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,226
<i>It won't be hard to raise him.</i>

71
00:03:47,936 --> 00:03:48,978
<i>Does he know?</i>

72
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:50,772
<i>We don't talk about it.</i>

73
00:03:50,855 --> 00:03:52,440
<i>What about Alex?</i>

74
00:03:53,107 --> 00:03:54,150
<i>He won't agree to this.</i>

75
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:55,360
<i>Amelia.</i>

76
00:03:56,277 --> 00:03:57,946
<i>If it were up to me,</i>

77
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:00,865
<i>I'd want them to become friends.</i>

78
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:04,911
<i>I want them to get along as brothers.</i>

79
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,996
<i>That's all I ask, Amelia.</i>

80
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,583
<i>When are we getting married?</i>

81
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:16,422
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

82
00:04:19,884 --> 00:04:21,344
[YOUNG ALEX]
<i>I didn't know you could box.</i>

83
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:23,054
<i>Who taught you?</i>

84
00:04:23,137 --> 00:04:24,180
<i>Papa taught me.</i>

85
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:25,890
<i>How about we do some sparring?</i>

86
00:04:25,974 --> 00:04:26,724
<i>Sure.</i>

87
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,518
[SOFT THUDS]

88
00:04:28,601 --> 00:04:29,602
<i>Wait. Time out!</i>

89
00:04:29,686 --> 00:04:31,104
<i>Boxers don't take breaks.</i>

90
00:04:33,189 --> 00:04:34,899
[AMELIA GASPS]<i> Alex!</i>

91
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:35,942
<i>Alex!</i>

92
00:04:36,025 --> 00:04:38,278
<i>Come on, dear.</i><i>Stand up.</i>

93
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:39,362
<i>Get up, son.</i>

94
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:41,781
<i>What did you do?!</i>

95
00:04:41,864 --> 00:04:43,825
<i>We were just doing some sparring.</i>

96
00:04:43,908 --> 00:04:46,536
<i>I didn't mean to hurt him.</i>

97
00:04:46,619 --> 00:04:49,330
<i>Why did you challenge Alex</i>
<i>to a sparring match?</i>

98
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:51,040
<i>I didn't. He did.</i>

99
00:04:51,499 --> 00:04:53,251
<i>How dare you talk back at me!</i>

100
00:04:53,876 --> 00:04:56,754
<i>It's okay, Ma. I just lost my balance.</i>

101
00:04:57,463 --> 00:05:00,258
<i>No, dear. I know what I saw.</i>

102
00:05:00,341 --> 00:05:03,094
<i>I want you to stop doing boxing, okay?</i>

103
00:05:03,177 --> 00:05:05,138
<i>Do you understand?</i>

104
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:06,514
<i>Let them do boxing.</i>

105
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:08,057
<i>Boxing isn't for you.</i>

106
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:09,392
[BADONG]<i> Amelia!</i>

107
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:11,019
<i>Hold your T-shirt.</i>

108
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:12,020
[KNOCKING ON METAL GATE]

109
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:15,481
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

110
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:16,316
<i>Hey.</i>

111
00:05:17,608 --> 00:05:18,943
<i>- Amelia.</i>
<i>- Yes?</i>

112
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:20,278
<i>It's Jessie.</i>

113
00:05:20,361 --> 00:05:21,779
<i>What about him?</i>

114
00:05:21,863 --> 00:05:23,865
<i>He suffered a heart attack</i>
<i>in the middle of the fight.</i>

115
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:24,741
<i>What?!</i>

116
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:31,664
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

117
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:51,309
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:05:51,809 --> 00:05:53,102
[AMELIA]<i> Hey, Victor.</i>

119
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:55,146
<i>Now that your father is gone,</i>

120
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:57,398
<i>you better know your</i><i>place here.</i>

121
00:05:57,482 --> 00:06:01,027
<i>You'll help around the house</i>
<i>and take care of Alex.</i>

122
00:06:01,110 --> 00:06:03,071
<i>Things are not the same anymore.</i>

123
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:04,280
<i>You can't just play as you wish.</i>

124
00:06:06,991 --> 00:06:09,827
Your father died before we got
the chance to get married.

125
00:06:11,245 --> 00:06:12,830
I only did it because…

126
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:16,626
I didn't want you to feel
inferior to Victor.

127
00:06:16,709 --> 00:06:18,002
[VICTOR SCOFFS]

128
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:22,048
I was just protecting you, dear.

129
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:24,258
Do you understand me?

130
00:06:24,342 --> 00:06:26,385
I did it to protect you.

131
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:27,261
Alex.

132
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:28,888
Alex, hear me out first.

133
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:29,764
It's not--

134
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:32,683
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,685
Is this what you want?

136
00:06:34,769 --> 00:06:37,021
For me and Alex to fight?

137
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:38,731
You ungrateful bastard!

138
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:41,067
- You're ungrateful!
- Tell me.

139
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:42,944
Is that how you see me?

140
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:46,030
The child you took in
who should feel indebted to you?

141
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:49,033
I spent more than the cost
of that property to raise you!

142
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:51,369
What happened to the money
that Papa left us?

143
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:53,287
You used it all on Alex's education.

144
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:55,581
What happened to the money
that Papa left for me?

145
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:57,333
Alex is smarter than you.

146
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:58,918
You're nothing but a troublemaker.

147
00:06:59,001 --> 00:07:01,504
And you got married early
so you didn't finish your studies.

148
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:03,631
You're no different than Liana.

149
00:07:03,714 --> 00:07:06,050
Don't even compare me to that woman!

150
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:08,052
Why are you so mad at her?!

151
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:09,512
Yes, I was the mistress.

152
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:12,140
I was your dad's mistress,
but he loved me.

153
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:16,227
You're just afraid of your own ghosts!

154
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,479
When your father courted me,

155
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:21,149
I didn't know he was already married.

156
00:07:21,983 --> 00:07:23,109
Our situation is different.

157
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:29,866
But why are you punishing me
for Papa's mistakes?

158
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:31,075
Huh?!

159
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:34,078
You never treated me as your son.

160
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:37,331
But I treated you like my mother!

161
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:40,418
I could have moved out of the house
if I'd wanted to.

162
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:42,170
I was old enough to.

163
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:46,007
But I didn't do it
because I considered you as family.

164
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:49,760
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:52,013
I waited for you to have
a change of heart,

166
00:07:52,096 --> 00:07:53,848
but it never happened.

167
00:07:53,931 --> 00:07:57,602
And even if I had known
all of that back then,

168
00:07:58,060 --> 00:08:00,646
I would still have seen you as my mother.

169
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:06,235
But now, I don't care anymore
whether you accept me or not

170
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,154
because you kept reminding me

171
00:08:08,237 --> 00:08:12,200
and throwing it in my face
that I was a bastard.

172
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:14,243
That it was all my mother's fault.

173
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:19,165
You even made me beg for
what should rightfully be mine!

174
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:21,751
Mine! They are mine!

175
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:26,923
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:28,633
I don't care anymore.

177
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:29,800
And this time…

178
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:34,388
I'll now claim what I deserve.

179
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:39,352
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:40,645
Victor.

181
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,271
Victor.

182
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:51,113
- [MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SOBBING]

183
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:59,622
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:40,830
All my life,
I've been living a lie, Liana.

185
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:43,624
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

186
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:46,043
Alex…

187
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:48,337
You didn't do anything wrong.

188
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:53,342
Her lies don't invalidate
who you are as a person…

189
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:56,887
and everything
you've achieved in your life.

190
00:09:56,971 --> 00:10:01,475
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:02,852
[SIGHS]

192
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:14,113
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:10:19,493 --> 00:10:20,745
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

194
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:29,462
And most importantly,

195
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:32,757
it will not change my love for you.

196
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:37,845
I will make sure our child never feels

197
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:39,972
what I'm feeling right now.

198
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:44,435
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

199
00:10:44,518 --> 00:10:49,815
No one will ever call our child a bastard.

200
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:53,569
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

201
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:56,030
[ALEX] Liana, I promise you…

202
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:01,827
I will marry you.

203
00:11:05,247 --> 00:11:06,415
I love you.

204
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:12,380
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

205
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:16,133
We just need to get Victor
out of our lives.

206
00:11:17,593 --> 00:11:19,095
Because that's the only way…

207
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:23,349
for us to be free and happy.

208
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:27,728
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

209
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:29,355
[JULIANA EXHALES HEAVILY]

210
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:43,244
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

211
00:11:53,170 --> 00:12:00,136
[SOBBING]

212
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:10,938
- [BANGING]
- [SCREAMS IN ANGER]

213
00:12:12,022 --> 00:12:19,071
- [STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SOBBING]

214
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:27,413
[PHONE RINGING]

215
00:12:27,496 --> 00:12:28,289
Grandma?

216
00:12:28,372 --> 00:12:30,040
Victor, we need to meet.

217
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:31,750
Okay. Why?

218
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:35,713
I have something to give you,
but it has to be in person.

219
00:12:35,796 --> 00:12:37,631
Where are we meeting?

220
00:12:37,715 --> 00:12:40,718
At the park, near the gym.

221
00:12:40,801 --> 00:12:42,303
I'm on my way.

222
00:12:42,386 --> 00:12:44,263
All right. Take care.

223
00:12:45,973 --> 00:12:47,975
Grandma, you're leaving?

224
00:12:48,058 --> 00:12:51,061
Uh, I won't take long. I'll be back soon.

225
00:12:52,271 --> 00:12:53,856
You're meeting with Victor?

226
00:12:53,939 --> 00:13:00,905
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

227
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,371
- [AMELIA] Alex, son…
- [THUD]

228
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:13,876
Believe me.

229
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:16,128
I didn't do it to hurt you.

230
00:13:17,046 --> 00:13:19,423
I would lie for you.

231
00:13:20,716 --> 00:13:22,927
I'm begging for your forgiveness, son.

232
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:25,513
I will do anything.

233
00:13:25,596 --> 00:13:27,765
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:28,891
Son--

235
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:31,185
[SOBBING]

236
00:13:34,104 --> 00:13:37,858
Maybe it's best
if you go back to your own house.

237
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:43,197
After all, you sacrificed a lot
for that house, right?

238
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,449
Son…

239
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:51,413
I hope you understand that I only did that

240
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:53,832
to get on Victor's good side.

241
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:56,919
I'm a bastard because of you!

242
00:13:58,837 --> 00:14:02,007
Shouldn't you have sympathy for me?!

243
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:05,386
You fell in love with a married woman!

244
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:10,266
My relationship with Juliana

245
00:14:10,349 --> 00:14:12,643
has nothing to do with your mistakes!

246
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:14,645
Nothing!

247
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:21,735
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:14:37,209 --> 00:14:39,003
Oh, Kate. You're home.

249
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:40,838
No one was around when I got here

250
00:14:40,921 --> 00:14:42,423
so I just made some snacks.

251
00:14:42,506 --> 00:14:43,549
Where's Grandma?

252
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:46,093
She left. Didn't you know?

253
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:49,305
Why? Where did she go?

254
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,724
I heard her talking to Victor.

255
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:55,519
She said she had to see him
to give him something.

256
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:58,230
What time did she leave?

257
00:14:58,314 --> 00:15:00,107
Just a while ago.

258
00:15:01,358 --> 00:15:05,362
Did she say where she was going?

259
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:10,159
They'll meet at the park
near Victor's gym.

260
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:11,118
Why?

261
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:34,099
Not now, Sylvia. I'm in a hurry.

262
00:15:35,184 --> 00:15:35,935
[YELPS]

263
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:37,019
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:15:37,102 --> 00:15:38,020
Why?

265
00:15:38,395 --> 00:15:40,189
You're off to see Alex again, aren't you?

266
00:15:40,689 --> 00:15:42,191
Didn't he leave just now?!

267
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:44,318
You think I don't know?

268
00:15:44,401 --> 00:15:46,737
You really can't get enough
of him, can you?

269
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:49,782
In case you've forgotten,
you're on my property, Sylvia.

270
00:15:49,865 --> 00:15:51,033
So keep your mouth shut.

271
00:15:51,116 --> 00:15:52,785
If there's something
that should be kept shut,

272
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:56,747
bound, and chained,
it should be your legs!

273
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,416
What do you want, huh?

274
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:01,543
I want to know how many times
I have to tell you

275
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,545
to stay away from my husband!

276
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:06,048
Where do you get the audacity
to keep doing this, huh?!

277
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:08,759
I swear, you'd better keep
your mouth shut, Sylvia.

278
00:16:08,842 --> 00:16:11,512
Don't blame me if your husband
keeps coming back to me.

279
00:16:11,595 --> 00:16:14,264
If you don't want him to do that,
tie him up!

280
00:16:14,348 --> 00:16:18,185
It's not my fault your husband
doesn't love you anymore!

281
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:20,521
- [SLAPS]
- [GROANS]

282
00:16:20,604 --> 00:16:22,398
- You flirt! How dare you?!
- [WHIMPERS]

283
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:24,483
- Come here! Come here!
- Stop it!

284
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:26,527
- Sylvia!
- Come here!

285
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,237
You're hurting me, Sylvia!

286
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,364
That's enough! Stop it!

287
00:16:30,447 --> 00:16:31,323
Come here!

288
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:33,409
- Stop it!
- You slut!

289
00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:36,245
Does it hurt that your husband
loves me more than you?!

290
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:38,080
Are you jealous, huh?!

291
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:39,832
- Sylvia!
- You whore! You whore!

292
00:16:39,915 --> 00:16:41,959
- [SYLVIA GRUNTS]
- [JULIANA WHIMPERS]

293
00:16:42,042 --> 00:16:43,919
[JULIANA] Ah!

294
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,172
You witch! How dare you?!

295
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:49,174
- I'm pregnant, you witch!
- [SYLVIA SCREAMS]

296
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:51,385
- I'm carrying a child!
- [SCREAMING CONTINUES]

297
00:16:51,468 --> 00:16:53,971
- [KATE] Hey! Stop it!
- [JULIANA] You witch!

298
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:55,806
Stop it! Juliana is pregnant!

299
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:59,226
I strongly suggest that
you keep that home-wrecker on a leash

300
00:16:59,309 --> 00:17:02,646
so she stops chasing after my husband
like a rabid dog!

301
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:05,149
I won't waste any more time
on you, Sylvia!

302
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,235
- Move!
- Juliana!

303
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:09,570
Move!

304
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:10,738
Hey!

305
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:15,701
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

306
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:20,330
Olivia.

307
00:17:20,956 --> 00:17:22,207
Take charge here, okay?

308
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:23,125
I'll meet with Grandma Pilar.

309
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:25,002
- [METAL CLANGS]
- [MAN] Aah!

310
00:17:25,085 --> 00:17:27,880
[SCREAMS IN PAIN]

311
00:17:27,963 --> 00:17:29,673
What happened, mister?

312
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:30,549
[MAN GROANS]

313
00:17:30,632 --> 00:17:32,217
- What happened?
- I have cramps.

314
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:34,053
Cramps? Let me help you.

315
00:17:34,928 --> 00:17:37,848
Sit down first. Is it your right foot?

316
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:39,725
- It hurts here.
- Hold on.

317
00:17:39,808 --> 00:17:41,393
I will stretch it, okay?

318
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:43,353
- Ready? Okay.
- Aah!

319
00:17:43,437 --> 00:17:44,813
[GROANS]

320
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:52,988
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

321
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:59,036
[CAR HORN HONKING]

322
00:18:15,719 --> 00:18:16,970
[GROANS]

323
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:21,767
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

324
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:22,684
[WHIMPERS]

325
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:28,273
[TIRES SCREECHING]

326
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:34,988
[BREATHING ANXIOUSLY]

327
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:42,079
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

328
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:56,677
Ah.

329
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:59,012
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

330
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:11,483
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

331
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:12,568
Grandma.

332
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:15,571
W-What are you doing here?

333
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:19,032
Grandma, why are you meeting Victor?

334
00:19:21,285 --> 00:19:23,787
Don't wait for him.
Come on. Let's go home.

335
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:25,247
It's too late.

336
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:31,044
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,045
What…

338
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:34,965
What do you mean?

339
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:44,892
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

340
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:52,024
[SEETHING]

341
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:58,030
I now have strong evidence
against Juliana and Alex.

342
00:20:02,826 --> 00:20:04,870
They won't be able to deny this.

343
00:20:04,953 --> 00:20:09,917
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

344
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,418
[HUFFS]

345
00:20:14,963 --> 00:20:16,423
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

346
00:20:16,506 --> 00:20:19,927
[STIRRING MUSIC SWELLS]

347
00:20:21,970 --> 00:20:23,680
Grandma Pilar sent me this.

348
00:20:31,438 --> 00:20:32,648
She's given up.

349
00:20:33,398 --> 00:20:37,152
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

350
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:40,280
She couldn't condone
their actions anymore.

351
00:20:40,364 --> 00:20:43,116
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

352
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:47,246
[VICTOR SIGHS DEEPLY]

353
00:20:47,329 --> 00:20:49,039
Why do I feel this way?

354
00:20:49,122 --> 00:20:54,211
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

355
00:20:54,294 --> 00:20:56,546
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

356
00:20:57,881 --> 00:21:01,760
I knew that they were having
an affair, but… [SNIFFLES]

357
00:21:01,843 --> 00:21:05,013
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

358
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:07,391
It feels different
when it's right in front of me.

359
00:21:11,061 --> 00:21:15,148
I don't know if I should be grateful.

360
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:17,025
[CRIES]

361
00:21:17,109 --> 00:21:20,821
Because I've finally opened my eyes to…
[SNIFFLES]

362
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:22,364
…everything they did behind my back.

363
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:24,825
[INHALES, EXHALES DEEPLY]

364
00:21:24,908 --> 00:21:26,994
[CRIES]

365
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:32,291
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

366
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:34,042
Or maybe…

367
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:43,051
it's all my fault.

368
00:21:46,596 --> 00:21:49,433
Because everyone I loved…

369
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:57,482
didn't even think twice about
screwing me over.

370
00:21:59,151 --> 00:22:00,610
How could you do this to me?

371
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:03,405
[CRIES] Why?

372
00:22:03,488 --> 00:22:04,823
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

373
00:22:04,906 --> 00:22:07,034
- Liana.
- [JULIANA CRYING]

374
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:09,536
You know how much I love you.

375
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:12,664
[PILAR] But the way you are now,

376
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:15,876
I'd rather have Victor raise Abby

377
00:22:15,959 --> 00:22:18,128
than let her grow up to be like you.

378
00:22:19,546 --> 00:22:22,215
I didn't do this to hurt you.

379
00:22:22,299 --> 00:22:25,886
I did it because
it's the right thing to do.

380
00:22:25,969 --> 00:22:28,847
But I'm your granddaughter.

381
00:22:28,930 --> 00:22:33,477
With what you did,
it's like you've just sent me to prison!

382
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,729
Is doing the right thing
more important to you

383
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:37,647
than saving your granddaughter?

384
00:22:37,731 --> 00:22:39,816
How could you do it, Grandma?

385
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:43,320
What you're doing to Victor is too much.

386
00:22:43,403 --> 00:22:47,199
Why did you do it, Grandma?
That will send me to jail!

387
00:22:47,282 --> 00:22:49,159
[JULIANA SOBBING]

388
00:22:49,242 --> 00:22:52,370
Liana, I just can't condone
your actions anymore.

389
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:55,540
[SOBBING]

390
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:56,958
- [GROANS]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

391
00:22:57,042 --> 00:22:59,044
- What's happening?
- [GROANING]

392
00:22:59,127 --> 00:23:00,879
- Sit down.
- Grandma!

393
00:23:00,962 --> 00:23:04,633
- Sit down--
- Let go of me! Let go of me!

394
00:23:04,716 --> 00:23:07,511
- [JULIANA GROANING]
- Help!

395
00:23:07,594 --> 00:23:10,347
- Hold on. Help!
- Let go of me!

396
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:12,974
Help! She needs to go to the hospital!

397
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:15,185
- [PILAR] Hurry! Be careful!
- I'm bleeding!

398
00:23:15,268 --> 00:23:17,562
Be careful. Help us!

399
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:21,316
Liana! Let's hurry! Come on!

400
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:25,320
Mama, Alex…
[CRIES, SNIFFLES]

401
00:23:25,403 --> 00:23:27,614
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

402
00:23:27,697 --> 00:23:30,200
[SIGHS]
…and Juliana.

403
00:23:33,328 --> 00:23:35,956
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

404
00:23:37,415 --> 00:23:40,252
I tried to give everything I could.

405
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:45,507
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

406
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:48,760
[INHALES SHARPLY, EXHALES DEEPLY]

407
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,722
But it's still not enough.

408
00:23:56,434 --> 00:23:58,270
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

409
00:23:58,353 --> 00:24:02,274
It wasn't enough to make them give me

410
00:24:02,357 --> 00:24:04,067
a little bit of respect.

411
00:24:04,151 --> 00:24:07,487
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

412
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:11,658
Victor.

413
00:24:15,328 --> 00:24:19,207
There is nothing wrong or missing in you.

414
00:24:21,418 --> 00:24:23,336
You simply fell in love.

415
00:24:24,754 --> 00:24:25,922
[SNIFFLES]

416
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:30,343
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

417
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:32,429
I know it hurts.

418
00:24:36,224 --> 00:24:38,685
I know you're hurting right now.

419
00:24:41,605 --> 00:24:43,732
But I believe that…

420
00:24:44,941 --> 00:24:48,111
you have to go through all of this.

421
00:24:48,195 --> 00:24:50,572
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

422
00:24:50,655 --> 00:24:55,368
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

423
00:24:55,452 --> 00:24:57,662
You know what? [SNIFFLES]

424
00:24:58,914 --> 00:25:01,208
Only a few people…

425
00:25:02,709 --> 00:25:07,297
are lucky enough to find
a beautiful truth.

426
00:25:08,506 --> 00:25:10,634
[OLIVIA] More often than not,

427
00:25:10,717 --> 00:25:14,387
the truth hurts.

428
00:25:14,471 --> 00:25:17,807
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

429
00:25:17,891 --> 00:25:19,351
It's ugly…

430
00:25:21,603 --> 00:25:23,730
and devastating.

431
00:25:27,817 --> 00:25:30,153
[SIGHS DEEPLY, SNIFFLES]

432
00:25:33,823 --> 00:25:35,325
[OLIVIA] But…

433
00:25:38,119 --> 00:25:40,789
it's what will set you free, Victor.

434
00:25:43,166 --> 00:25:46,253
[INHALES, EXHALES DEEPLY]

435
00:25:46,336 --> 00:25:50,757
It's what will give you
the strength to move on.

436
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:54,761
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

437
00:25:54,844 --> 00:25:57,597
- [SNIFFLES]
- [EXHALES DEEPLY]

438
00:25:57,681 --> 00:25:59,933
And because of it,

439
00:26:00,016 --> 00:26:04,062
you will find the right people for you.

440
00:26:13,446 --> 00:26:15,824
It was true when I said that…

441
00:26:17,867 --> 00:26:20,245
I'll always be by your side.

442
00:26:20,328 --> 00:26:27,335
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

443
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:49,482
[DOOR OPENS]

444
00:26:53,111 --> 00:26:53,862
[PHONE BUZZING]

445
00:26:53,945 --> 00:26:56,114
GRANDMA PILAR

446
00:26:56,197 --> 00:27:01,786
[PHONE BUZZING]

447
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:08,918
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

448
00:27:38,448 --> 00:27:45,538
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SHOWER RUNNING]

449
00:28:00,553 --> 00:28:07,519
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

450
00:28:11,564 --> 00:28:12,565
Sylvia?

451
00:28:34,921 --> 00:28:41,886
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

452
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:57,777
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

453
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:22,844
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

454
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:25,430
[PHONE BUZZING]

455
00:29:27,515 --> 00:29:28,349
Hello, Grandma?

456
00:29:28,975 --> 00:29:29,851
Hello, Alex?

457
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:32,771
Yes, I've been trying to call you
since last night.

458
00:29:32,854 --> 00:29:33,813
What's wrong?

459
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:35,648
Something happened to Juliana.

460
00:29:35,732 --> 00:29:37,609
She's in the hospital.

461
00:29:37,692 --> 00:29:40,069
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

462
00:29:40,153 --> 00:29:42,739
Make sure you eat a lot, okay?

463
00:29:42,822 --> 00:29:45,825
Auntie, where are Grandma and Mommy?

464
00:29:46,910 --> 00:29:49,370
Uh, they just went somewhere.

465
00:29:50,705 --> 00:29:52,123
Do you want this?

466
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:53,500
Yes.

467
00:29:53,583 --> 00:29:55,877
Will they be gone for a long time?

468
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:58,463
Can we go see Daddy?

469
00:29:58,546 --> 00:30:01,633
Daddy's just in the gym, right?

470
00:30:01,716 --> 00:30:02,884
Huh?

471
00:30:02,967 --> 00:30:05,178
I'll ask your mommy first, okay?

472
00:30:05,261 --> 00:30:07,597
Go on, eat up. Eat a lot, okay?

473
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:14,103
[PHONE RINGING]

474
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:18,775
Hello, Grandma? How's Juliana?

475
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:21,277
What should I say to Abby?

476
00:30:21,361 --> 00:30:24,030
She's asking where her mom is.

477
00:30:24,113 --> 00:30:26,658
How do I tell her
that she's in the hospital?

478
00:30:27,742 --> 00:30:29,744
Mommy is in the hospital?

479
00:30:30,829 --> 00:30:33,248
What happened to Mommy?

480
00:30:33,331 --> 00:30:40,255
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

481
00:30:47,595 --> 00:30:48,596
Liana.

482
00:30:49,681 --> 00:30:51,432
[GROANS SOFTLY] Grandma?

483
00:30:51,516 --> 00:30:58,022
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

484
00:30:58,106 --> 00:30:59,107
Hold on.

485
00:30:59,816 --> 00:31:01,276
I'll call the doctor.

486
00:31:01,818 --> 00:31:03,111
G-Grandma…

487
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:07,282
How's my baby?

488
00:31:09,284 --> 00:31:11,035
[BREATH QUIVERING]

489
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:12,370
W-Where's my baby?

490
00:31:12,453 --> 00:31:16,916
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

491
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,209
Grandma…

492
00:31:20,795 --> 00:31:21,880
Grandma.

493
00:31:22,672 --> 00:31:24,090
[SOBBING]

494
00:31:24,173 --> 00:31:25,174
It's gone.

495
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,844
The baby is gone.

496
00:31:28,386 --> 00:31:30,138
- What?
- The baby is gone.

497
00:31:30,221 --> 00:31:33,182
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

498
00:31:33,266 --> 00:31:37,687
N-No, no. No. No…

499
00:31:37,770 --> 00:31:40,565
Let's go see my baby.

500
00:31:40,648 --> 00:31:42,525
Let's talk to the doctor.

501
00:31:42,609 --> 00:31:44,444
- Grandma. No, Grandma!
- The baby's gone.

502
00:31:44,527 --> 00:31:46,487
Don't say that!

503
00:31:46,571 --> 00:31:49,073
Don't ever say that! My baby is alive!

504
00:31:50,283 --> 00:31:54,037
Grandma, no. This cannot be!

505
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:57,540
I already lost a child once!
This can't be happening!

506
00:31:57,624 --> 00:32:00,877
Let me talk to the doctor.
Let me talk to the doctor!

507
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:01,711
Grandma!

508
00:32:01,794 --> 00:32:04,839
It's not true! It's not true!

509
00:32:04,923 --> 00:32:09,135
Take back what you said!
It's not true, Grandma!

510
00:32:09,218 --> 00:32:10,470
I have to go to Abby.

511
00:32:10,553 --> 00:32:12,430
Kate called me.
She said the kid's worried.

512
00:32:12,513 --> 00:32:13,890
They also went to the hospital.

513
00:32:13,973 --> 00:32:18,102
Okay, but do you think they know
what Ms. Pilar did, Victor?

514
00:32:18,186 --> 00:32:21,189
Maybe it's the reason why
Juliana is in the hospital.

515
00:32:21,814 --> 00:32:25,443
I don't know why Juliana's in there.

516
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:30,365
I'm just worried that
you might bump into Alex there.

517
00:32:31,282 --> 00:32:33,409
Juliana might not want you there.

518
00:32:34,118 --> 00:32:36,996
Olivia, I'm not going to
the hospital to start a fight.

519
00:32:38,706 --> 00:32:41,668
I also know how painful it is
to lose a child.

520
00:32:41,751 --> 00:32:44,379
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

521
00:32:44,462 --> 00:32:46,756
I'm going there because Abby needs me.

522
00:32:48,174 --> 00:32:50,134
I have to go.
You take care of things here.

523
00:33:12,448 --> 00:33:13,241
Dear?

524
00:33:18,121 --> 00:33:20,999
Say hi to your mom.

525
00:33:23,334 --> 00:33:26,462
Uh, Liana. We'll leave you two alone.

526
00:33:27,255 --> 00:33:28,256
Kate.

527
00:33:31,134 --> 00:33:32,176
Mommy.

528
00:33:34,721 --> 00:33:37,515
I came here with Aunt Kate.

529
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:41,227
Are you okay, Mommy?

530
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:45,982
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

531
00:33:46,065 --> 00:33:48,943
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

532
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:50,445
Come here, dear.

533
00:33:52,447 --> 00:33:54,407
[GRUNTS] Sit next to Mommy.

534
00:33:55,324 --> 00:33:56,617
[SNIFFLES]

535
00:33:56,701 --> 00:33:57,952
[JULIANA] Uh…

536
00:34:00,038 --> 00:34:02,290
I'm not okay, baby.

537
00:34:04,459 --> 00:34:06,294
[JULIANA BREATHES DEEPLY]

538
00:34:06,377 --> 00:34:08,337
Mommy is sad.

539
00:34:08,421 --> 00:34:09,839
Why?

540
00:34:12,091 --> 00:34:13,551
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

541
00:34:13,634 --> 00:34:15,053
Because…

542
00:34:16,137 --> 00:34:17,680
Mommy's baby…

543
00:34:20,141 --> 00:34:22,894
is now in heaven with your brother, Marco.

544
00:34:22,977 --> 00:34:25,438
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

545
00:34:25,521 --> 00:34:27,774
Mommy is sad because…

546
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:31,569
we lost the baby.

547
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:35,490
[SNIFFLES]

548
00:34:36,407 --> 00:34:38,409
Don't cry, Mommy.

549
00:34:38,493 --> 00:34:40,661
- I'm still here.
- [SOBBING]

550
00:34:40,745 --> 00:34:43,748
I'll be your baby again.

551
00:34:45,291 --> 00:34:52,298
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES,
THEN FADES]

552
00:34:53,883 --> 00:34:56,469
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

553
00:34:56,552 --> 00:35:03,559
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

554
00:35:29,335 --> 00:35:36,259
[SULLEN MUSIC CONTINUES]

555
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:39,846
Juliana.

556
00:35:40,763 --> 00:35:43,099
Alex… Alex.

557
00:35:43,182 --> 00:35:46,018
[SORROWFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

558
00:35:46,102 --> 00:35:47,186
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

559
00:35:48,479 --> 00:35:55,486
[SOBBING]

560
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:59,115
Alex, our baby is gone.

561
00:36:01,033 --> 00:36:02,618
We lost our baby.

562
00:36:02,702 --> 00:36:09,709
- [SOBBING]
- [SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

563
00:36:26,225 --> 00:36:27,685
I'm sorry, Juliana.

564
00:36:27,768 --> 00:36:31,355
[SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

565
00:36:31,439 --> 00:36:37,570
[SOBBING]

566
00:36:37,653 --> 00:36:38,654
I'm sorry.

567
00:36:43,951 --> 00:36:50,917
[PHONE RINGING]

568
00:36:52,668 --> 00:36:53,669
Hello?

569
00:36:55,129 --> 00:36:56,130
Ms. Pilar?

570
00:37:01,469 --> 00:37:08,476
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

571
00:37:10,728 --> 00:37:11,771
[THUDS]

572
00:37:13,522 --> 00:37:20,446
- [GRUNTING, SCREAMING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

573
00:37:20,529 --> 00:37:23,366
- [KICKS LANDING]
- [SCREAMING]

574
00:37:23,449 --> 00:37:24,992
- [BLOW LAND]
- [GRUNTING]

575
00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:26,244
[SCREAMS] Aah!

576
00:37:29,747 --> 00:37:32,124
<i>Grandma gave Victor a copy of the video.</i>

577
00:37:33,167 --> 00:37:34,919
<i>The video on her cell phone.</i>

578
00:37:35,544 --> 00:37:37,463
[BREATH QUIVERING]

579
00:37:37,546 --> 00:37:40,383
<i>It's proof of our relationship.</i>

580
00:37:41,592 --> 00:37:44,178
<i>I went after Grandma, but…</i>

581
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:47,139
<i>I didn't make it in time.</i>

582
00:37:48,683 --> 00:37:52,103
<i>Sylvia saw me while I was leaving.</i>

583
00:37:53,187 --> 00:37:54,272
<i>That's when she attacked me.</i>

584
00:37:54,355 --> 00:37:56,774
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

585
00:37:56,857 --> 00:37:57,817
[SOBS]

586
00:37:59,694 --> 00:38:02,280
[JULIANA BREATHES DEEPLY]

587
00:38:02,822 --> 00:38:03,906
<i>Alex…</i>

588
00:38:04,949 --> 00:38:06,033
[SNIFFLES]

589
00:38:06,993 --> 00:38:07,868
[INHALES DEEPLY]

590
00:38:07,952 --> 00:38:09,537
<i>Alex, I don't want to go to jail.</i>

591
00:38:12,707 --> 00:38:14,208
<i>And most importantly…</i>

592
00:38:15,042 --> 00:38:17,586
<i>I don't want Victor to have Abby.</i>

593
00:38:19,338 --> 00:38:21,090
<i>My daughter is mine.</i>

594
00:38:21,924 --> 00:38:23,217
<i>Just mine.</i>

595
00:38:24,176 --> 00:38:26,804
[JULIANA SNIFFLING, SOBBING]

596
00:38:28,931 --> 00:38:29,932
[SMOOCHES]

597
00:38:36,897 --> 00:38:43,654
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

598
00:38:49,952 --> 00:38:52,288
It's the result of your disbarment case.

599
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:04,800
[PAPER RIPPING]

600
00:39:08,512 --> 00:39:09,764
[SCREAMS] Aah!

601
00:39:14,435 --> 00:39:15,436
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

602
00:39:16,645 --> 00:39:17,646
[DOOR OPENS]

603
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:19,523
Alex…

604
00:39:21,650 --> 00:39:26,113
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

605
00:39:27,782 --> 00:39:29,075
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

606
00:39:29,158 --> 00:39:30,659
What are you doing here?

607
00:39:33,245 --> 00:39:34,580
Are you happy now?

608
00:39:36,457 --> 00:39:37,666
Is this what you wanted?

609
00:39:41,379 --> 00:39:43,798
I didn't want this to happen, Liana.

610
00:39:46,467 --> 00:39:49,595
I once thought of your child as ours.

611
00:39:52,264 --> 00:39:54,350
I could never take joy in this.

612
00:39:55,434 --> 00:39:58,062
Even though it was the result
of your affair with Alex.

613
00:39:58,145 --> 00:40:01,732
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

614
00:40:01,816 --> 00:40:04,360
I know Grandma gave you
a copy of the video.

615
00:40:04,443 --> 00:40:05,611
What will you do now?

616
00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:08,489
You'll use it against us in court, huh?

617
00:40:11,784 --> 00:40:12,868
Victor…

618
00:40:14,537 --> 00:40:16,580
I've already lost my child, Victor.

619
00:40:16,664 --> 00:40:19,375
Isn't that enough punishment?

620
00:40:22,378 --> 00:40:24,338
Let's end this!

621
00:40:24,422 --> 00:40:26,090
Let's end this now, please!

622
00:40:27,258 --> 00:40:28,092
[JULIANA] Let me go!

623
00:40:28,175 --> 00:40:30,136
Let's just live our separate lives.

624
00:40:30,219 --> 00:40:31,595
Let me go!

625
00:40:33,264 --> 00:40:34,473
[JULIANA SOBBING]

626
00:40:34,557 --> 00:40:38,018
I'm begging you, Victor. Let me go.

627
00:40:40,521 --> 00:40:44,733
Leave me alone. Let's end this now.

628
00:40:44,817 --> 00:40:51,824
- [JULIANA SOBBING]
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

629
00:41:11,010 --> 00:41:17,975
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

630
00:41:26,025 --> 00:41:33,032
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

631
00:41:33,657 --> 00:41:35,284
[OBJECTS CLATTERING, GLASS BREAKING]

632
00:41:38,037 --> 00:41:41,207
[OBJECTS CLATTERING, GLASS BREAKING]

633
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:43,626
[SYLVIA] Alex!

634
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:46,337
Alex, what's going on?

635
00:41:47,379 --> 00:41:48,589
[SYLVIA GASPS]

636
00:41:49,298 --> 00:41:51,217
[ALEX] How dare you attack Juliana?!

637
00:41:51,967 --> 00:41:53,677
How dare you attack Juliana?!

638
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:55,513
[GRUNTS]

639
00:41:56,263 --> 00:41:57,681
Can you blame me?!

640
00:41:59,058 --> 00:42:02,728
I saw you coming out of their place

641
00:42:02,811 --> 00:42:04,855
in broad daylight!

642
00:42:06,232 --> 00:42:08,150
You're still continuing your affair!

643
00:42:12,821 --> 00:42:15,199
My child with Juliana is gone.

644
00:42:17,451 --> 00:42:19,745
She had a miscarriage!

645
00:42:19,828 --> 00:42:26,752
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

646
00:42:26,835 --> 00:42:28,170
Alex…

647
00:42:28,254 --> 00:42:29,255
[SYLVIA GASPS]

648
00:42:32,716 --> 00:42:34,385
Are you blaming me?

649
00:42:35,761 --> 00:42:38,097
It was you who didn't honor our agreement!

650
00:42:39,974 --> 00:42:42,726
You said you would stop
your affair with Juliana,

651
00:42:42,810 --> 00:42:44,562
but what did you do?!

652
00:42:46,146 --> 00:42:47,773
You didn't stop!

653
00:42:48,524 --> 00:42:50,359
You didn't let her go!

654
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:52,319
[SYLVIA GASPS]

655
00:42:52,403 --> 00:42:59,368
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

656
00:43:02,204 --> 00:43:03,914
- [SYLVIA SCREAMS]
- [VASE SHATTERS]

657
00:43:05,708 --> 00:43:06,875
[GROANS]

658
00:43:09,587 --> 00:43:13,882
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

659
00:43:13,966 --> 00:43:15,509
Alex. Alex--

660
00:43:15,593 --> 00:43:17,386
Don't touch me!

661
00:43:20,097 --> 00:43:23,142
[SOBBING]

662
00:43:23,225 --> 00:43:26,061
Alex, I'm not a bad person!

663
00:43:27,062 --> 00:43:30,357
I'm not a bad person, Alex.
I just loved you!

664
00:43:30,441 --> 00:43:32,026
You don't own me!

665
00:43:32,568 --> 00:43:34,945
I gave you one last chance,

666
00:43:35,904 --> 00:43:38,574
but you still chose that woman!

667
00:43:42,411 --> 00:43:44,079
Maybe you deserve each other.

668
00:43:44,163 --> 00:43:51,170
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

669
00:43:58,135 --> 00:43:59,553
[SCREAMS] Aah!

670
00:44:08,270 --> 00:44:15,277
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

671
00:44:23,494 --> 00:44:25,162
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

672
00:44:32,211 --> 00:44:34,588
[KEYPAD CLACKING]

673
00:44:36,590 --> 00:44:38,300
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

674
00:44:38,384 --> 00:44:40,469
[LINE RINGING]

675
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:42,805
Attorney.

676
00:44:45,015 --> 00:44:46,225
I want to talk to you.

677
00:44:46,308 --> 00:44:50,312
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

678
00:44:59,071 --> 00:45:00,864
Eat up so you can regain your strength.

679
00:45:03,367 --> 00:45:05,494
Matteo said…

680
00:45:05,577 --> 00:45:08,372
the result of your disbarment case
has been released.

681
00:45:10,707 --> 00:45:13,168
Let's not talk about that.
What matters is your wellbeing.

682
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:16,505
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

683
00:45:22,428 --> 00:45:23,512
What are you doing here?

684
00:45:29,268 --> 00:45:32,312
I'm here to clear things up
between the three of us.

685
00:45:34,565 --> 00:45:35,315
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

686
00:45:36,024 --> 00:45:38,026
I'm ready to withdraw
the charges against both of you.

687
00:45:38,110 --> 00:45:42,406
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

688
00:45:42,489 --> 00:45:44,950
[VICTOR] As long as Abby stays with me.

689
00:45:45,033 --> 00:45:47,035
And don't try what you did to me before

690
00:45:47,119 --> 00:45:49,329
because I'm talking to you nicely.

691
00:45:49,413 --> 00:45:53,584
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

692
00:45:53,667 --> 00:45:56,086
Do you think I'll agree, huh?!

693
00:45:59,673 --> 00:46:01,800
I don't want our daughter
to have a messy life.

694
00:46:04,803 --> 00:46:07,222
I'm not going to take her
away from you, Liana.

695
00:46:07,306 --> 00:46:09,349
I just want to be with her
until she grows up.

696
00:46:09,433 --> 00:46:10,767
No!

697
00:46:10,851 --> 00:46:13,312
My daughter stays with me!
I won't allow it, Victor!

698
00:46:15,189 --> 00:46:17,316
If I present the evidence I have in court,

699
00:46:17,399 --> 00:46:19,276
what do you think will happen to you?

700
00:46:19,359 --> 00:46:20,611
You will go to jail.

701
00:46:20,694 --> 00:46:22,321
And who will Abby go to?

702
00:46:23,322 --> 00:46:24,781
[ALEX] Fine.

703
00:46:24,865 --> 00:46:26,158
I'll prepare everything that's needed.

704
00:46:26,241 --> 00:46:28,911
I'll file a petition in court
for you to get custody of Abby.

705
00:46:29,786 --> 00:46:31,371
[JULIANA] Alex, what are you saying?

706
00:46:31,705 --> 00:46:34,458
Abby is mine! My daughter
will stay with me! Stop!

707
00:46:34,541 --> 00:46:35,626
That's enough.

708
00:46:35,709 --> 00:46:37,503
This will settle things between us.

709
00:46:37,586 --> 00:46:41,089
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

710
00:46:41,173 --> 00:46:42,758
You won. You can leave.

711
00:46:42,841 --> 00:46:49,806
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [JULIANA BREATHING HEAVILY]

712
00:46:49,890 --> 00:46:52,643
Don't do that!
My daughter will stay with me.

713
00:46:52,726 --> 00:46:55,437
Abby is mine. She's ours. Stop this!

714
00:46:56,313 --> 00:46:58,148
Trust me. I'll take care of it.

715
00:46:58,690 --> 00:47:02,819
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

716
00:47:02,903 --> 00:47:09,910
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

717
00:47:24,007 --> 00:47:31,056
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

718
00:47:35,894 --> 00:47:42,943
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

719
00:47:50,909 --> 00:47:53,704
[HANGERS CLATTERING]

720
00:47:56,248 --> 00:47:57,749
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

721
00:47:57,833 --> 00:47:58,834
No.

722
00:48:00,961 --> 00:48:01,962
No!

723
00:48:03,463 --> 00:48:04,756
No…

724
00:48:04,840 --> 00:48:06,174
No!

725
00:48:06,258 --> 00:48:12,806
[SOBBING]

726
00:48:12,889 --> 00:48:16,935
No, no, no, no…

727
00:48:17,019 --> 00:48:20,814
- [STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SOBBING CONTINUES]

728
00:48:20,897 --> 00:48:22,691
No!

729
00:48:24,401 --> 00:48:25,402
No.

730
00:48:28,155 --> 00:48:30,032
No!

731
00:48:31,074 --> 00:48:32,326
Thank you, Attorney.

732
00:48:37,289 --> 00:48:38,832
Have you talked to your lawyer?

733
00:48:39,666 --> 00:48:42,169
The transfer of Abby's custody
has been filed.

734
00:48:44,046 --> 00:48:45,547
I've withdrawn the case.

735
00:48:46,548 --> 00:48:48,383
How did you convince Juliana?

736
00:48:50,344 --> 00:48:52,262
Don't ask too many questions.

737
00:48:52,346 --> 00:48:54,431
Just don't talk to her about this.

738
00:48:56,350 --> 00:48:57,351
Now, what?

739
00:48:57,434 --> 00:48:58,644
You're free now.

740
00:48:59,686 --> 00:49:01,104
Go get Abby.

741
00:49:01,897 --> 00:49:04,274
From today on, I have no brother.

742
00:49:04,358 --> 00:49:06,943
We're out of each other's lives.

743
00:49:07,027 --> 00:49:13,992
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

744
00:49:18,330 --> 00:49:20,415
Why didn't you tell me?

745
00:49:20,499 --> 00:49:23,669
Alex, what did you do?
Did you forge my signature?

746
00:49:24,378 --> 00:49:26,588
Alex, speak up! What have you done?!

747
00:49:27,255 --> 00:49:30,384
The important thing is that
Victor will withdraw the case against us.

748
00:49:30,967 --> 00:49:32,469
We won't go to jail.

749
00:49:33,053 --> 00:49:35,305
We'll get Abby back eventually.

750
00:49:36,431 --> 00:49:38,183
Do you hear yourself?

751
00:49:38,850 --> 00:49:42,604
I can't afford to lose my child
even for a second.

752
00:49:43,605 --> 00:49:47,401
Alex, you don't understand,
I can't lose a child again.

753
00:49:47,484 --> 00:49:49,986
You won't lose Abby.
She won't be taken away.

754
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:51,863
You can still visit her.

755
00:49:51,947 --> 00:49:53,448
Abby is my daughter.

756
00:49:54,116 --> 00:49:55,534
She's mine!

757
00:49:56,201 --> 00:49:59,121
I won't reach the point of begging Victor

758
00:49:59,204 --> 00:50:02,374
just to be with my child
because she's mine!

759
00:50:03,041 --> 00:50:05,085
She's mine. I gave birth to her.

760
00:50:05,168 --> 00:50:07,754
I brought her up. I raised her.

761
00:50:07,838 --> 00:50:09,506
Just me, me, me!

762
00:50:09,589 --> 00:50:11,258
Trust me on this one, Liana.

763
00:50:11,341 --> 00:50:12,342
Trust me.

764
00:50:13,009 --> 00:50:15,637
Victor may have won the battle
but not the war.

765
00:50:17,264 --> 00:50:18,265
Please.

766
00:50:19,391 --> 00:50:20,642
[JULIANA SOBS]

767
00:50:21,560 --> 00:50:24,813
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

768
00:50:24,896 --> 00:50:27,941
Just make sure you keep your promise.

769
00:50:31,778 --> 00:50:33,989
Because Abby is important to me.

770
00:50:35,866 --> 00:50:37,534
Abby is my life.

771
00:50:40,036 --> 00:50:42,372
She's the only one I can call mine.

772
00:50:43,498 --> 00:50:49,254
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

773
00:50:51,715 --> 00:50:54,760
Alex, I'm fine. I can walk on my own.

774
00:50:54,843 --> 00:50:56,595
It's for the better.

775
00:50:56,678 --> 00:50:58,930
The doctor also said you need to rest.

776
00:51:03,351 --> 00:51:04,436
Thank you.

777
00:51:08,607 --> 00:51:09,691
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

778
00:51:11,985 --> 00:51:13,236
I've moved out.

779
00:51:14,946 --> 00:51:17,741
I'm looking for a place where we can stay,

780
00:51:17,824 --> 00:51:19,409
just like we planned before.

781
00:51:22,537 --> 00:51:23,663
Alex…

782
00:51:25,916 --> 00:51:27,501
At what cost?

783
00:51:30,086 --> 00:51:31,963
We may be together, but…

784
00:51:32,631 --> 00:51:34,633
we've lost so much.

785
00:51:36,176 --> 00:51:37,594
Our child…

786
00:51:38,804 --> 00:51:40,305
your career as a lawyer.

787
00:51:40,388 --> 00:51:43,391
It's not the end of the world
now that I'm no longer a lawyer.

788
00:51:44,601 --> 00:51:46,812
I can do many things, Juliana.

789
00:51:47,896 --> 00:51:49,523
We'll start over.

790
00:51:49,606 --> 00:51:51,358
Everything will be all right.

791
00:51:52,234 --> 00:51:54,820
As long as we're together,
that's what matters.

792
00:51:54,903 --> 00:51:57,030
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

793
00:51:57,113 --> 00:51:58,114
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

794
00:52:00,909 --> 00:52:01,993
You know…

795
00:52:03,912 --> 00:52:06,998
[JULIANA] I don't know what
I'd do without you by my side.

796
00:52:10,669 --> 00:52:12,921
Forget about the thought of losing me

797
00:52:13,004 --> 00:52:14,589
because it will never happen.

798
00:52:14,673 --> 00:52:18,134
I will love you and stay with you

799
00:52:18,218 --> 00:52:19,928
for the rest of my life.

800
00:52:20,011 --> 00:52:22,889
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

801
00:52:22,973 --> 00:52:24,558
[JULIANA, ALEX CHUCKLE SOFTLY]

802
00:52:36,194 --> 00:52:37,279
[SYLVIA] Victor.

803
00:52:39,155 --> 00:52:40,323
[VICTOR SIGHS HEAVILY]

804
00:52:42,158 --> 00:52:44,911
I'm ready to testify
against Alex and Juliana.

805
00:52:46,705 --> 00:52:47,706
[SCOFFS]

806
00:52:48,957 --> 00:52:50,709
I've already dropped the case.

807
00:52:53,336 --> 00:52:54,337
What?

808
00:52:55,922 --> 00:52:57,549
Why did you do that?!

809
00:52:58,717 --> 00:53:00,635
Didn't you say…

810
00:53:00,719 --> 00:53:04,264
we can't just let them be happy
after everything they've done?!

811
00:53:04,347 --> 00:53:06,516
They deserve nothing, Victor!

812
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:08,351
Victor, don't be a fool!

813
00:53:09,019 --> 00:53:11,187
They shouldn't get away with
what they've done to us!

814
00:53:11,271 --> 00:53:13,565
They have to pay!
They have to go to prison!

815
00:53:13,648 --> 00:53:14,983
Sylvia, can you stop?!

816
00:53:16,234 --> 00:53:17,903
Do what you want.

817
00:53:18,737 --> 00:53:20,614
But I won't help you.

818
00:53:21,364 --> 00:53:22,824
I already have my daughter,

819
00:53:22,908 --> 00:53:24,951
and that's all that matters to me.

820
00:53:25,035 --> 00:53:27,871
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

821
00:53:27,954 --> 00:53:33,293
[SOBBING]

822
00:53:34,169 --> 00:53:40,884
[BREATHING RAGGEDLY]

823
00:53:40,967 --> 00:53:43,094
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

824
00:53:43,178 --> 00:53:45,472
[GUESTS CLAPPING]

825
00:53:46,598 --> 00:53:49,225
<i>I can put up with you having an affair,</i>

826
00:53:49,309 --> 00:53:51,102
<i>but Juliana?</i>

827
00:53:53,521 --> 00:53:54,689
<i>Really?!</i>

828
00:53:56,566 --> 00:53:59,194
<i>I will end things with Juliana.</i>

829
00:54:00,487 --> 00:54:03,073
<i>The doctor said I'll have</i>
<i>a hard time getting pregnant.</i>

830
00:54:04,699 --> 00:54:10,163
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

831
00:54:10,246 --> 00:54:12,999
<i>I may not be able to give you</i>
<i>the family you want.</i>

832
00:54:13,083 --> 00:54:14,084
<i>Sorry, ma'am.</i>

833
00:54:14,668 --> 00:54:17,087
<i>I've decided to keep my baby.</i>

834
00:54:20,131 --> 00:54:22,926
<i>Alex, our baby…</i>

835
00:54:23,009 --> 00:54:27,722
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

836
00:54:27,806 --> 00:54:31,184
[SOBBING]

837
00:54:31,267 --> 00:54:34,145
<i>Am I really the father of</i>
<i>the baby Juliana is carrying?</i>

838
00:54:34,229 --> 00:54:36,982
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

839
00:54:37,065 --> 00:54:38,066
[SMACK]

840
00:54:39,067 --> 00:54:41,027
<i>You knew I was the father</i>
<i>of Juliana's baby,</i>

841
00:54:41,111 --> 00:54:42,737
<i>but you kept it from me!</i>

842
00:54:42,821 --> 00:54:46,074
<i>Don't blame me if your husband</i>
<i>doesn't love you anymore!</i>

843
00:54:46,157 --> 00:54:46,992
[SMACK]

844
00:54:47,742 --> 00:54:48,910
- [SMACK]
- [SYLVIA GASPS]

845
00:54:48,994 --> 00:54:51,955
<i>- You shameless woman!</i>
- [JULIANA WHIMPERING] <i>Stop!</i>

846
00:54:52,038 --> 00:54:54,708
<i>You said you would end things</i>
<i>with Juliana!</i>

847
00:54:54,791 --> 00:54:56,751
<i>But what did you do?!</i>

848
00:54:56,835 --> 00:54:58,670
<i>You didn't stop!</i>

849
00:54:59,546 --> 00:55:01,089
<i>You carried on with your affair!</i>

850
00:55:02,173 --> 00:55:03,174
[GASPING]

851
00:55:03,258 --> 00:55:06,469
<i>I will love you and stay with you</i>

852
00:55:06,553 --> 00:55:08,263
<i>for the rest of my life.</i>

853
00:55:08,346 --> 00:55:13,351
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

854
00:55:13,435 --> 00:55:18,106
[SOBBING]

855
00:55:33,204 --> 00:55:35,623
[AMELIA] <i>If only you were alive, Jessie,</i>

856
00:55:36,666 --> 00:55:39,044
<i>I would have someone</i>
<i>to share my problems with.</i>

857
00:55:40,670 --> 00:55:42,464
But I won't give up.

858
00:55:42,547 --> 00:55:46,968
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

859
00:55:47,052 --> 00:55:49,554
I'll do anything for Alex.

860
00:55:52,557 --> 00:55:54,642
Just like I promised you…

861
00:55:55,810 --> 00:55:58,354
I'm going to take care of Alex.

862
00:55:58,438 --> 00:56:02,442
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

863
00:56:02,525 --> 00:56:04,277
[INHALES DEEPLY]

864
00:56:05,195 --> 00:56:06,613
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

865
00:56:07,781 --> 00:56:09,074
How are you, dear?

866
00:56:09,157 --> 00:56:10,784
- Don't worry, Dad.
- [THUNDER RUMBLES]

867
00:56:10,867 --> 00:56:12,160
I'm fine.

868
00:56:12,786 --> 00:56:15,330
You know my stand on this.

869
00:56:15,413 --> 00:56:18,083
You don't have to stay with Alex, Sylvia.

870
00:56:19,042 --> 00:56:21,044
You have nothing to worry about, Dad.

871
00:56:21,669 --> 00:56:22,921
I know what I'm doing.

872
00:56:23,546 --> 00:56:25,965
This problem will soon end.

873
00:56:26,758 --> 00:56:28,009
Please trust me.

874
00:56:28,885 --> 00:56:31,638
I just don't want you
to keep getting hurt.

875
00:56:31,721 --> 00:56:33,932
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

876
00:56:34,015 --> 00:56:35,350
I'll be fine, Dad.

877
00:56:36,101 --> 00:56:38,269
Okay. I trust you.

878
00:56:39,646 --> 00:56:42,232
Just call me if there's a problem, okay?

879
00:56:43,066 --> 00:56:44,025
[SYLVIA] <i>Dad…</i>

880
00:56:44,109 --> 00:56:44,984
Hmm?

881
00:56:46,444 --> 00:56:47,695
[VOICE BREAKING] I love you.

882
00:56:48,696 --> 00:56:50,156
I love you too.

883
00:56:50,740 --> 00:56:57,038
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

884
00:56:58,456 --> 00:57:01,084
You finally got custody of Abby.

885
00:57:01,167 --> 00:57:04,254
You no longer have to worry that
she'll be taken away from you.

886
00:57:04,337 --> 00:57:07,924
We'll help you so Abby can adjust easily.

887
00:57:09,175 --> 00:57:10,426
Thank you, guys.

888
00:57:11,052 --> 00:57:13,555
Oh, right. I'll pick up Abby later.

889
00:57:14,264 --> 00:57:16,266
So, let's celebrate later?

890
00:57:17,475 --> 00:57:19,310
- [OLIVIA] I'll cook.
- [CHUCKLES]

891
00:57:19,394 --> 00:57:20,395
[BADONG] All right.

892
00:57:20,854 --> 00:57:22,313
I'll buy beer.

893
00:57:22,397 --> 00:57:24,190
- [LAUGHS]
- [OLIVIA CHUCKLES]

894
00:57:24,566 --> 00:57:27,402
- Maybe just a few, Coach.
- [BADONG] Right.

895
00:57:27,485 --> 00:57:34,534
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

896
00:57:39,956 --> 00:57:42,584
What if we just share custody of her?

897
00:57:42,959 --> 00:57:44,294
So it will be equal.

898
00:57:46,045 --> 00:57:49,424
This is not the right time
for you to haggle with Victor.

899
00:57:50,175 --> 00:57:54,095
Let's plan things out
once he gets custody of Abby.

900
00:57:54,179 --> 00:58:01,186
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

901
00:58:26,961 --> 00:58:34,010
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

902
00:59:03,873 --> 00:59:04,791
Abby?

903
00:59:06,709 --> 00:59:09,128
I'm done packing, Mommy.

904
00:59:10,213 --> 00:59:13,007
Just like Uncle Alex told me.

905
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:16,344
Grandma Pilar helped me as well.

906
00:59:21,474 --> 00:59:25,937
Can't we just stay with Daddy, Mommy?

907
00:59:27,021 --> 00:59:29,190
I don't want to leave you.

908
00:59:29,983 --> 00:59:34,028
I promised I'd stay by your side.

909
00:59:34,112 --> 00:59:38,866
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

910
00:59:38,950 --> 00:59:40,034
Dear…

911
00:59:41,244 --> 00:59:43,037
You're not going anywhere, okay?

912
00:59:43,121 --> 00:59:46,124
You'll stay here with me.

913
00:59:46,916 --> 00:59:48,626
Really?

914
00:59:48,710 --> 00:59:50,253
But…

915
00:59:50,336 --> 00:59:53,673
What about Uncle Alex and Daddy?

916
00:59:55,383 --> 00:59:57,635
Wouldn't they be angry?

917
00:59:58,344 --> 01:00:00,597
I don't care if they get angry.

918
01:00:01,973 --> 01:00:03,057
I'll deal with them.

919
01:00:03,141 --> 01:00:05,018
Don't worry, okay?

920
01:00:05,101 --> 01:00:08,271
All that matters is we're together.

921
01:00:09,355 --> 01:00:12,692
What's really going on, Mommy?

922
01:00:13,484 --> 01:00:16,237
Why do I have to choose
between you and Daddy?

923
01:00:16,321 --> 01:00:18,031
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

924
01:00:18,114 --> 01:00:21,784
I love both you and Daddy.

925
01:00:22,452 --> 01:00:24,996
[BREATH QUIVERS]

926
01:00:25,079 --> 01:00:26,080
Abby…

927
01:00:27,290 --> 01:00:28,583
Stop crying, okay?

928
01:00:28,666 --> 01:00:31,044
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

929
01:00:31,127 --> 01:00:36,174
Your daddy and I
may not agree on a lot of things,

930
01:00:36,257 --> 01:00:39,469
but that doesn't mean we don't love you.

931
01:00:42,055 --> 01:00:45,892
I… I don't want to lose you, dear.

932
01:00:45,975 --> 01:00:48,311
Stay with Mommy, okay?

933
01:00:49,270 --> 01:00:50,730
I love you so much.

934
01:00:50,813 --> 01:00:52,315
[ABBY SOBBING]

935
01:00:52,398 --> 01:00:53,358
I love you, Abby.

936
01:00:53,441 --> 01:00:55,610
I love you too, Mommy.

937
01:00:56,277 --> 01:01:01,866
- [BOTH SOBBING]
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

938
01:01:01,949 --> 01:01:03,743
Let's just meet on Sunday.

939
01:01:03,826 --> 01:01:04,827
Okay?

940
01:01:06,245 --> 01:01:07,622
Huh? But-- Wait!

941
01:01:07,705 --> 01:01:09,874
- I have to go. Bye!
- [ZEUS BARKING]

942
01:01:10,541 --> 01:01:11,626
Zeus!

943
01:01:13,169 --> 01:01:14,295
Huh?

944
01:01:15,588 --> 01:01:16,714
Zeus, what are you…?

945
01:01:17,715 --> 01:01:18,800
[GASPS]

946
01:01:18,883 --> 01:01:21,344
[SCREAMING]

947
01:01:21,427 --> 01:01:24,222
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]
- [MAID WHIMPERING]

948
01:01:24,305 --> 01:01:25,056
[VICTOR] Sylvia!

949
01:01:25,139 --> 01:01:28,476
[WHIMPERING]

950
01:01:28,559 --> 01:01:34,774
[MAID SCREAMING]

951
01:01:34,857 --> 01:01:41,114
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

952
01:01:41,197 --> 01:01:42,407
What have you done?!

953
01:01:42,490 --> 01:01:49,455
- [MAID WAILING]
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]
